<font color="#FF0000">...A LIFETIME</font><br>
<tt>Sat Dec  6 23:30:10 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I feel alive today. <br><br>
The trees even looked different, and I found myself &quot;seeing&quot; things that I had passed by many times, and never noticed.<br><br>
Life is like that. I mourn what I haven't &quot;seen&quot; for the past 27 years, but rejoice that I have the opportunity to begin again. Not many people ever get a second chance at life. They pass through and end as they begun, the stuff of stardust, and no memory remains of their passage.<br><br>
I now see people and relationships in a light that I do not quite understand, but it feels real good. Feelings surface that do not yet have names, but it does not matter. I can feel, something that I lost a long time ago very far away, that is now coming home.<br><br>
I will use this &quot;here&quot; time to re-define myself. I like that. If I succeed for only a minute, the happiness will be a lifetime.<br><br>
Art <br><br>

